<p>The businesswoman returned to social media earlier this month after taking time out to focus on her health following surgery on her two broken feet.</p>

<p>She revealed she feared her injury would leave her 'paralysed' after she plummeted 25ft off a wall at a theme park in Turkey and landed on her feet.  </p>

<p>The CBB star explained how her feet are 'destroyed' following the incident, and admitted she has returned to The Priory to learn to 'walk again.'</p>

<p>Katie, who was on holiday with Carl and her children Princess, 13, and Junior, 15, at the time, said doctors told her they have amputated legs with injuries similar to hers.</p>

<p>Speaking to The Sun, she said: 'The doctors said I'm lucky I'm not dead. I could have hit my head and I could have been paralysed, I am actually lucky I landed on my feet. </p>

<p>'I thought, "I'm never going to walk again". The doctors said they've cut off legs before after seeing injuries like mine.' </p>

